( Bot Hunter Analysis Report) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
( 1. Executive Summary) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Bot Hunter analysed 149,239 click events.) Tj
T*
(It selected 3,731 as likely bot traffic, which is 2.50% of the run.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(This report should be read as evidence for review, not as proof of fraud for) Tj
T*
(every individual event. The dataset does not include ground-truth labels, so the) Tj
T*
(probability figures are operational confidence estimates rather than measured) Tj
T*
(precision or recall.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The submitted output is submission.tsv. It keeps the required binary) Tj
T*
(is_bot decision and adds an operational tier so the same prediction can be) Tj
T*
(used more carefully in business workflows.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
( 2. What The System Does) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Bot Hunter combines two complementary classifiers.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(- Rules-based classifier: transparent rules that identify repeated,) Tj
T*
(  mechanically timed, or tightly clustered click patterns.) Tj
T*
(- Machine-learning classifier: an Extended Isolation Forest anomaly model over 14) Tj
T*
(engineered behavioural features.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The final score is a weighted blend:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(text) Tj
T*
(combined_score = \(0.58 * heuristic_score\) + \(0.42 * ml_score\)) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The rules layer is weighted slightly higher because it is easier to explain and) Tj
T*
(audit. The anomaly model still matters because it can identify unusual) Tj
T*
(combinations that a small rule set may not capture.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
( 3. Main Results) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The strongest explainable patterns in this run were:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(- repeated query: 3,403 events) Tj
T*
(- repeated query/domain pair: 2,086 events) Tj
T*
(- confirmed query repetition: 2,023 events) Tj
T*
ET
endstream
