() Tj
T*
(| Rule strength | Meaning | Score treatment |) Tj
T*
(|---|---|---|) Tj
T*
(| Strong | Direct mechanical or replay evidence | Contributes its full rule weight |) Tj
T*
(| Supporting | Contextual or weaker evidence | Capped together at 0.24 |) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The exact time-to-click reuse rule uses a 99th-percentile reuse-count threshold) Tj
T*
(with an absolute floor. The main repetition and concentration rules also use) Tj
T*
(99th-percentile batch thresholds with the previous fixed count and total-rate) Tj
T*
(cutoffs kept as guardrails. This lets the rules adapt to the observed) Tj
T*
(population while avoiding weak duplicate counts in small runs.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The ct rule, confirmed query repetition, and dense burst repetition rules are) Tj
T*
(conjunctive. In practical terms, they require multiple signals to be present) Tj
T*
(before adding score. This is safer than treating broad context, such as) Tj
T*
(country-like concentration, as a standalone bot indicator.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The anomaly classifier uses the engineered feature matrix. The main feature) Tj
T*
(families are:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(- region/browser/OS frequency) Tj
T*
(- global ct country frequency) Tj
T*
(- sub-200 ms click flags) Tj
T*
(- local burst density) Tj
T*
(- query entropy) Tj
T*
(- query, domain, and query/domain repetition counts) Tj
T*
(- same-second and exact time-to-click reuse counts) Tj
T*
(- timing magnitude after log transformation) Tj
T*
(- low-cardinality kp and sld value frequencies) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(High-volume domain frequency and global country frequency are down-weighted to) Tj
T*
(0.50 and 0.50, respectively. The low-cardinality) Tj
T*
(kp and sld frequency features are down-weighted to 0.50 and) Tj
T*
(0.25. Events isolated quickly by random hyperplane splits receive higher anomaly scores.) Tj
T*
(EIF is the only production anomaly model; alternate ML backends and supervised pilots) Tj
T*
(have been removed.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(kp and sld are treated as categorical-style assumptions rather than true) Tj
T*
(continuous measurements because their observed cardinality is very low. Raw) Tj
T*
(kp and sld values remain in the feature artefact for audit, but the anomaly) Tj
T*
(model uses log_kp_count and log_sld_count instead of raw numeric distances.) Tj
T*
(The raw values are excluded from ml_feature_names.) Tj
T*
ET
